 BY BAMIDELE FAMOOFO The Board of Directors of Guinness Nigeria Plc has disclosed its intention to present its half year financial results for the period ended December 31, 2021 to investors through the Nigerian Exchange Limited on January 27, 2022. The Board disclosed that it will hold a on Wednesday, 26 January 2022 for the purpose of considering and approving the financial results for the quarter ended 31st December 2021, amongst other matters. “Accordingly, in compliance with the NGX Rules and the Amendments to the Listing Rules, the closed period for trading in the Company’s shares by insiders commenced on the 31st of December 2021 and will expire 24 hours after the announcement of the results,” Guinness said in a letter to the NGX. Therefore, no Director, person discharging managerial responsibility, employees with sensitive information and other insiders of the company and their connected persons may directly or indirectly deal in the securities of the company during the closed period. 